quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  4,163,"We have sent revelation to you [Prophet] as We did to Noah and the prophets who came after him, to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and the Tribes, to Jesus, Job, Jonah, Aaron, and Solomon and David, to whom We gave the Psalms"
  4,164,"We have told you about some messengers sent previously, while We have not yet told you about others. God spoke to Moses directly"
  4,165,"They were messengers, bearing good news and giving warning, so that mankind would have no excuse before God, after the coming of the messengers. God is mighty, wise"
  4,166,But God bears witness to what He has sent down to you. He has sent it down with His knowledge. The angels too bear witness. And God suffices as a witness
  4,167,Those who are bent on denying the truth and on turning others away from the path of God have strayed far from the right path
  4,168,"God will not forgive those who deny the truth and act wrongfully, nor will He guide them"
  4,169,"to any path other than the path of Hell, wherein they shall abide forever. That is easy enough for God"
  4,170,"Mankind! The Messenger has brought you the truth from your Lord, so believe for your own good. And if you deny the truth, know that to God belongs all that the heavens and the earth contain. God is all knowing and wise"